creditline: Gift of Elizabeth, Julie, and Catherine Andrus in memory of John and Marion Andrus
description:
12 scenes depicting the labors of Hercules, matted and framed together:

19a. Pauli, Hollstein 98 i/v  monogram and date in plate at lower right: [1542 HSB] inscribed in plate at top: [AERVMNAE HERCVLIS]
19b. Pauli, Hollstein 99 ii/ii  monogram and date in plate at lower left: [1548 HSB]
inscribed in plate at top: [LEONIS SUFFOCATI EXVVIIS INDVITVR HERCVLES]
19c. Pauli, Hollstein 100 i/iv  monogram and date in plate at upper right: [1545 HSB]
inscribed in plate at top: [HERCVLES VNA CVM IOLAO HYDRAM OCCIDIT]
19d. Pauli, Hollstein 101 iiii/iii  monogram and date in plate at upper left: [1545 HSB]
inscribed in plate at top: [GADITANAS COLVMNAS STATVIT HERCVLES]
19e. Pauli, Hollstein 102 ?/iv  monogram and date in plate at upper left: [1545 HSB]
inscribed in plate at top: [CACVM FLAMMIVOMVM OPPRIMIT HERCVLES]
19f. Pauli, Hollstein 103 i/iv  monogram and date in plate at lower left: [1545 HSB]
inscribed in plate at top: [ANTAEVM LIBIAE GYGANTEM SVFFOCAT HERCVLES]
19g. Pauli, Hollstein 104 i-ii/iii  monogram and date in plate at bottom center: [1545 HSB]
inscribed in plate at top: [HERCVLES CERBERVM TRICIPITEM AD SVPEROS PERTRAXIT]
19h. Pauli, Hollstein 105 i/iii  monogram in plate at lower right: [HSB]; date in plate at lower left: [1545] 
inscribed in plate at top: [HERCVLES MVLTIS BELLIS LACESSIT TROIAM]
19i. Pauli, Hollstein 106 v/v monogram and date in plate at upper left: [1542 HSB]; inscribed in plate at upper left: [HERCVLIS]
19j. Pauli, Hollstein 107 ii/iv  monogram and date in plate at upper center: [1544 HSB]
inscribed in plate at top: [EVRYTI REGIS FILIAM IOLAM, OCCISO PATRE, ABDVXIT HERCVLES]
19k. Pauli, Hollstein 108 i/ii  monogram and date in plate at lower left: [1542 HSB]
inscribed in plate at top: [DEIANIRA NESSI VESTEM PER LICHAM SERVVM HERCVLI MITTIT]
19l. Pauli, Hollstein 109 i/ii  monogram and date in plate at upper center: [1544 HSB]
inscribed in plate at top: [NESSI VESTE RABIDVS SE COMBVRIT HERCVLES / PHILOCRASSES]
marks: Signature, Date, Inscription Diverse locations for HSB monogram, dates, and ins
title: Labors of Hercules
